# External product links (GitHub, PyPI)

## Components

- **`ProductExternalLink`** (`@/components/ProductExternalLink`): use for outbound links whose destination is **GitHub** (`kind="github"`) or **PyPI** (`kind="pypi"`). By default renders **icon + visible label** (`children`). Use **`showIcon={false}`** when the parent already shows the product icon (e.g. contact page `ContactRow` with `IconGithub`); keep the same `href`/`kind`/`variant` for one implementation path.
- **`TeamMemberSocialLinks`**: use for **compact social rows** on team cards. **Icon-only** buttons with `aria-label` and `title` from the link label; classifies `pypi.org` / `github.com` (and other kinds) automatically.

## When to use which pattern

- **Icon + text** (`ProductExternalLink`): project “Links” sections, footer, prose (team page, inline sentences). Clearer for scanning and avoids relying only on brand recognition.
- **Icon-only** (`TeamMemberSocialLinks`): dense per-person link strips. Standard for social-style rows; labels must stay in **`aria-label` and `title`** (already set from `label`).

## Variants (`ProductExternalLink`)

- `inline` — project link lists and similar body copy.
- `footer` — site footer GitHub org link.
- `prose` — emphasized inline sentences (e.g. team intro).

## Do / don’t

- Do **not** use a plain `<a>` for GitHub/PyPI org or package URLs when `ProductExternalLink` applies—including with `showIcon={false}` if an icon sits in the parent row.
- Do **not** drop accessible names on icon-only links: keep `aria-label` / `title` (as in `TeamMemberSocialLinks`).
